 Central Venous Catheter Placement: You will first have a central venous catheter (CVC) placed.

 A CVC is a sterile flexible tube that will be placed into a large vein while you are under local anesthesia.

 Your doctor will explain this procedure to you in more detail, and you will be required to sign a separate consent form for it.

 The chemotherapy, some of the other drugs in this study, and the cord blood transplant will be given by vein through your CVC.

 Blood samples will also be drawn through your CVC.

 The CVC will remain in your body for about 2-5 months.

