 Fludarabine/Clofarabine/Busulfan/Rituximab/Total Body Irradiation: If you are between 1 and 80 years of age and can receive high-dose chemotherapy, and your doctor agrees, you will receive fludarabine, clofarabine, busulfan, ATG, total body irradiation, and possibly rituximab.

 If you are receiving this study plan medication, blood may be drawn to check levels of busulfan 1 or more times over the 4-day course of treatment.

